name: Inside the Freemasons
overview: With unique and unprecedented access to one of the world's oldest social networking societies this series asks who are the Freemasons and what do they do?

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: As the United Grand Lodge of England celebrates its 300th anniversary the secretive organisation throws open the doors of its wood-panelled rooms to show some of what goes on behind-the-scenes.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: Cameras capture one of the most important ceremonies in Freemasonry as two men undertake their Second Degree ceremony to become Fellow Craft Masons. Two members organise a charity boxing event.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: The most powerful of all Masonic rituals comes under the spotlight.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Freemasons reveal why they joined the brotherhood. Plus, it's the annual ladies' night in Bedford and a new music-themed lodge opens in South Wales.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Liverpool player Adam Lallana's Freemason father David opens a football-themed lodge as the world's oldest fraternity looks for new ways to attract members.
